{"_id":"silverslippers001","name":"Dorothea's Silver Slippers","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Magical silver slippers worn by Dorothea (OZena) that grant extraordinary mobility powers. The wearer can move through folds in space, disappearing and reappearing in a flash. Can teleport freely up to 30 feet without anyone preventing movement, but must be able to see the point of arrival. Once per Scene, can take a longer journey and reappear in any place previously seen at least once. These magical shoes are famous from the second witch Johanne that OZena killed.","quantity":1,"weight":1,"value":3000,"equipped":true,"properties":["Magical footwear","Teleportation up to 30 feet","Long-range teleport once per Scene","Must see destination","Taken from witch Johanne"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"elderberry001","name":"Elderberry Sprig","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Rare elderberry plant sprig, crucial missing ingredient for completing the Infusion of Purity. Elderberry does not grow in the Rot area of the Black Forest. Helga had small stash from her last trip. During Dorothea's fight with Manycorpses greenhouse creature, she grabbed this sprig in the chaos and escaped. Can be retrieved from Dorothea's green cape thrown carelessly in corner of room where she is imprisoned. Without this ingredient, the Infusion cannot be completed and blood curse cannot be broken.","location":"Dorothea's green cape in Helga's mansion","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"hammerhelm001","name":"Hammerhead Helmet","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Heavy and distinctive helmet worn by the Hammerheads, Helga's enslaved mercenaries. Helmet opens like flower on shoulders, granting total head and chest protection. Wearer immune to any wound that cannot penetrate thick layer of metal. Enemies can aim at lower body parts to bypass helmet protection, but receive 1 Penalty on their Check. The Hammerheads were once ferocious team of skilled mercenaries, now tamed by Helga's blood magic to serve her will.","quantity":1,"weight":15,"value":600,"equipped":true,"properties":["Heavy armor","Head and chest protection","Opens like flower","Immune to head wounds","Lower body vulnerable"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"helgablood001","name":"Helga's Blood Vials","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Vials containing Helga's magical blood used to enslave and control people. The Porcelain Princess carries five or six vials for newcomers to drink. Swallowing even one drop makes victim totally subject to Helga's will. Victims can be commanded like puppets, forced to perform any action. Eyes of enslaved show slight crimson tinge. Wolfgang uses blood drops to animate forest trees as guardian traps. Can be used to control plants and people's bodies with blood magic. Only Infusion of Purity can break the curse.","quantity":6,"weight":0.5,"value":400,"equipped":false,"properties":["Blood magic","Mind control substance","Enslaves drinkers to Helga","Animates plants","Crimson eye tinge on victims"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"hotairballoon001","name":"Henkle's Hot-Air Balloon","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Hot-air balloon made of patched fabric constructed by Norman Henkle inside huge oak tree molded into shape of grotesque castle. Device from future (1900) never before seen in 1780. Henkle plans to board balloon to activate incomplete Compass Rose and return to his time. Accumulates Time Tokens based on Hunter actions - when third Time Token placed, balloon is ready for takeoff. If Henkle activates incomplete Rose from balloon, huge tornado will hit entire Black Forest, affecting everyone and taking Henkle to unknown place.","quantity":1,"weight":200,"value":1500,"equipped":false,"properties":["Flying device from future","Made of patched fabric","Inside tree castle","Escape vehicle","Activates Compass Rose"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"penicillin001","name":"Henkle's Penicillin","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Modern medicine from year 1900 brought by Norman Henkle from the future. Doctor's bag contains Penicillin which Henkle used to halt epidemic in village of Smaragd. This miraculous cure elevated him to status of holy man among villagers. Along with wishing well powers, this established Henkle's authority and reputation as powerful wizard. Medicine from future is impossible to replicate in 1780 Black Forest, making it invaluable and irreplaceable.","quantity":5,"weight":0.5,"value":2000,"equipped":false,"properties":["Future medicine","From year 1900","Cures epidemic","Miraculous healing","Impossible to replicate in 1780"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"infusionpurity001","name":"Infusion of Purity","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Special potion that breaks Helga's blood magic curse. Produced at Helga's greenhouse from rare ingredients: Burdock, Nettle, Hyssop, and Elderberry. The potion renders anyone immune to Blood Magic for the course of a Scene and cancels mind control effects. Those under Blood Magic influence have slight crimson tinge to their eyes. Helga planned to sell this antidote to rich and powerful nobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. Missing Elderberry prevents completion.","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"value":800,"equipped":false,"properties":["Anti-magic potion","Breaks blood curse","Grants immunity for one Scene","Cancels mind control","Requires: Burdock, Nettle, Hyssop, Elderberry"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"helgakey001","name":"Key to Helga's Palace","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Key to enter Helga's well-maintained palace in village of Rot. Only building in village not dilapidated. Heavy reinforced door and barred windows make entry difficult. Porcelain Princess holds this key as Helga's favorite and cult manager. Can be obtained by defeating Princess or persuading her away from Helga's service. No one can come before Helga without approval of Porcelain Princess. Entering without key means encountering Hammerheads guards.","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"value":100,"equipped":false,"properties":["Palace access","Held by Porcelain Princess","Bypasses Hammerhead guards","Heavy reinforced door","Required for entry"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"compassrose001","name":"Margareta's Compass Rose Piece","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"One quarter of the Compass Rose, a powerful artifact capable of summoning storms that can throw people and objects into other worlds and dimensions. This piece was possessed by Margareta Westen, the witch of the West in the Black Forest. The four Black Forest witches (Johanne-East, Margareta-West, Helga-South, Karina-North) split the artifact into four parts so no one could abuse its power. OZena is hunting each witch to reassemble the complete Compass Rose.","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"value":5000,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical artifact","Part of complete Compass Rose","Can summon dimensional storms","Possessed by Western witch","Requires all 4 pieces to activate"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"porcelainmasks001","name":"Porcelain Doll Masks","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Grotesque porcelain doll masks worn by members of Helga's cult, the Crimson Kiss. Guards wear these distinctive masks while serving the Porcelain Princess, Helga's favorite who manages the cult. The Princess herself wears a beautiful doll mask to cover her disfigured face, hoping Helga will heal her appearance. Masks are symbols of the cult's devotion and obedience to the Red Witch. Each guard armed differently and highly dangerous.","quantity":10,"weight":1,"value":50,"equipped":false,"properties":["Cult symbol","Covers disfigurement","Mark of Crimson Kiss","Worn by guards","Porcelain material"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"mirrorwishes001","name":"The Mirror of a Thousand Wishes","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"One of the many treasures from the Order's Treasury kept in Valea Viilor fortified church, Transylvania. Inspired by Snow White's magic mirror. User can spend 1 Soma to see near past or imminent future of someone met at least once. Mirror shows moments on its surface. Observer doesn't know if viewing past or future (Storyteller secretly rolls: 1-3=past, 4-6=future). Same subject cannot be observed twice in one Scene. Alternatively, before attempting task, owner can spend 1 Soma, roll die, and on 4+ sees future moments granting 3 Additional Successes for first action. Special Order support item to anticipate OZena's movements.","quantity":1,"weight":3,"value":4000,"equipped":false,"properties":["Order's Treasure","Magical scrying","Shows past or future","Costs 1 Soma per use","Grants premonition bonus"],"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"wishingwell001","name":"The Wishing Well of Smaragd","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Ancient wishing well in center of Smaragd village whose true nature inhabitants always ignored. After centuries of inactivity, awakened by Henkle's own desire to become magician. Now grants Henkle power to make people's wishes come true, but his madness twists every wish with tainted results. Villagers make wishes hoping to fix Henkle's previous corrupted wishes, trapped in endless cycle of warped desires. Well is source of Henkle's magical powers and all aberrations in Smaragd.","location":"Center of Smaragd village in Black Forest","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
